SIMPLE: adopter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adopter
<hw>A*dopt"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who adopts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A receiver, with two necks,
opposite to each other, one of which admits the neck of a retort, and
the other is joined to another receiver. It is used in distillations, to
give more space to elastic vapors, to increase the length of the neck of
a retort, or to unite two vessels whose openings have different
diameters.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>adapter</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adoption</ent>⟦br⟧
